---
// Security Hall of Fame — advertised by SECURITY.md and
// /.well-known/security.txt (RFC 9116 Acknowledgments), so this URL must
// exist (claim-integrity, scorecard row #19). Ported from the retired
// apps/coming-soon stub.
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base
  title="Security Hall of Fame — nlqdb"
  description="Researchers who have responsibly disclosed security issues to nlqdb."
  canonical="/security/hall-of-fame"
>
  <main class="hof">
    <p class="hof__nav"><a href="/">← nlqdb</a></p>

    <h1>Security Hall of Fame</h1>

    <p>
      Thanks to the researchers below for responsibly disclosing security
      issues to nlqdb. Listing here is opt-in — we ask before adding anyone,
      and we use only the name or handle the researcher chooses.
    </p>

    <p>
      Want to report something? Email
      <a href="mailto:security@nlqdb.com">security@nlqdb.com</a>. We
      acknowledge within 72 hours, fix confirmed issues within 90 days, and
      credit reporters here at their request.
    </p>

    <h2>Researchers</h2>
    <p><em>No reports yet. Be the first.</em></p>

    <p class="hof__note">
      nlqdb is pre-revenue and does not currently operate a paid bug-bounty
      program. We may, at our sole discretion, offer a token of thanks for
      exceptional reports, but credit on this page is the standard
      recognition.
    </p>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .hof {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.25rem 5rem;
  }
  .hof__nav {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .hof h1 {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .hof h2 {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }
  .hof p {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .hof__note {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    font-size: 0.85em;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
</style>
